Following the killing of Iranian military commander, Gen. Qasem Soleimani in a United States (U.S.) airstrike in Iraq, the Inspector-General (IG) of Police Mohammed Adamu, has placed commands and formations on the red alert nationwide. Gen. Soleimani spearheaded Iranian military operations in the Middle East as head of Iran’s elite Quds Force before he was killed by the airstrike on January 3. In a statement yesterday by the Force Public Relations Officer (FPRO), Force Headquarters, Abuja, Frank Mba, a Deputy Commissioner (DCP), the police said the measure followed intelligence report sequel to the killing of the Iranian military chief. The statement reads: “This proactive measure follows Intelligence Report that sequel to the recent killing of an Iranian General; some domestic interests are planning to embark on massive public disturbances and sabotage. “Consequently, Zonal AIGs and Command Commissioners of Police have been directed to ensure maximum surveillance and security of lives and property across the nation. “The Police Commanders have been directed to ensure strategic deployments of both overt and covert Police operatives to ensure adequate security and safety of citizens, foreigners especially diplomats and diplomatic missions domiciled in Nigeria as well as the protection of critical national assets. “Meanwhile, the IGP has assured all Nigerians and foreigners resident in Nigeria of adequate security. He has equally warned all potential troublemakers to steer clear of the streets and territory of Nigeria.”